%N A396178 Lexicographically earliest sequence of the form 1, 2, followed by squarefree semiprimes (A006881), with the property that (a) for all k>=0, a(k) shares a factor with exactly k other terms, and (b) for all k >= 1, a(k) is divisible by a prime which does not divide any earlier term.
%C A396178 This is the same as A395795 except that the latter has a(1) = 4. Although the latter sequence has historical precedence, its definition was initially conjectural, and the present sequence is both simpler and belongs to a family of sequences (which is why the database now contains both versions).
%Y A396178 Cf. A006881, A392373, A395360, A395795.
%K A396178 nonn
